    "updated_at": "2025-05-07T09:48:05Z",
    "body": "This really breaks python virtualenv/venv things if you're using the `$VIRTUAL_ENV` to set the current venv session onto your prompt. (the activation script in, say: `./venv/bin/activate.fish` uses `set -gx` hence the reason for this). \n\nIf there's a workaround for this please let me know as well, as it is quite a necessity for this functionality to work.",
